-- Xcel Energy Halts Gas to Colorado Neighborhood After Explosion
-- B y   M a r k   C h e d i a k
-- 2013-06-13T19:23:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-13/xcel-energy-halts-gas-to-colorado-neighborhood-after-explosion.html
Xcel Energy Inc. (XEL)  has halted natural
gas service to a neighborhood in Westminster, Colorado, after a
blast destroyed one home.  Xcel and local emergency officials are responding to the
explosion, Gabriel Romero, a spokesman for the company, said in
a phone interview today. The utility will start its
investigation into the cause of the incident after the
“situation has been addressed from a safety standpoint.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
